	<Title>
		Can sit-ups flatten your stomach?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Abdominal exercises, such as sit-ups and crunches, can help strengthen abdominal muscles and improve posture. But you can&apos;t spot reduce areas of excess body fat with certain exercises. So if you have excess fat in your abdomen, don&apos;t count on crunches for six-pack abs. To lose weight and body fat, you need to consume fewer calories than you burn by adjusting your diet and exercise habits.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
